Searching records - default search

1. By default, EMu searches matching words and it's case-insensitive

At DMNS we have multiple collections by department, and every user is able to perform searches across all of these collections. This is why is important to understand how to search for what you are looking for.

2. Open any module to search. Here we opened the Catalog (VP).

We are logged in as Earth Sciences Collections Manager, but we still are able to search across collections.

3. Type "invertebrates" in the "Collection" field text box

Since EMu searches are case-insensitive, the results will be the same, no matter if you search with upper or lowercases.

4. Click the "Search icon"
5. See the results and note the "Collection" field

At first, we see results in the "Marine Invertebrates" collection in the "Zoology" department.

6. Click "Page down" to scroll the results
7. Note the results at the end of the page

You will see that, by default, EMu just searched for records in any collection with "Invertebrates" in the name. It also finds collections in the "Education Collections" department.
